# Cricket Player Segmentation using K-Means Clustering

This project applies **K-Means Clustering** to cricket player statistics to identify groups of players with similar batting performances. The dataset was preprocessed, cleaned, and transformed before clustering to uncover hidden patterns among players.

## Features
- Data Cleaning and Preprocessing
- Feature Engineering (Career Experience Calculation)
- Outlier Analysis
- Feature Scaling using StandardScaler
- Optimal Cluster Selection using:
  - Elbow Method
  - Silhouette Score
- K-Means Clustering
- 2D and 3D Cluster Visualization

## Tech Stack
- Python
- Pandas
- NumPy
- Matplotlib
- Seaborn
- Scikit-Learn
- Plotly

## Workflow
Data Collection → Data Cleaning → Feature Engineering → Scaling → Cluster Analysis → Visualization

## Results
Players were successfully grouped into distinct clusters based on their batting statistics, enabling comparative analysis of different player profiles and performance patterns.

